EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO STATE AFFAIRS AND GOVERNMENT -- DETENTION FOR FEDERAL
CIVIL IMMIGRATION VIOLATIONS
***
1 This act would prohibit any state or municipal government official or agency from
2 entering into any contract to detain individuals for civil immigration violations, and if any such
3 contract is in existence, the contract must be terminated by July 1, 2026. It would further prohibit
4 the use of any public resources to detain individuals for federal civil immigration violations.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
